-- British Sky, Corio, EDP, Fiat, Grifols: European Equity Preview
-- B y   T a r a   L a c h a p e l l e
-- 2010-11-05T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/british-sky-corio-edp-fiat-grifols-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  advanced 1.6 percent to 270.83.
The  Stoxx 50 Index  rose 1.7 percent to 2,590.70. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, gained 1.9
percent to 2,884.21.  Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA  (BMPS IM),  Intesa
Sanpaolo SpA  (ISP IM),  UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM), are among the
eight banks fined by Italy’s antitrust regulator for restricting
competition in the distribution of MasterCard Inc. credit cards.
MasterCard was penalized 2.7 million euros ($3.8 million), with
the banks together facing fines for the remainder of 3.3 million
euros in total penalties, the regulator said on its website
today.  Monte Paschi gained 2.1 percent to 97.2 cents, Intesa rose
1.5 percent to 2.49 euros, UniCredit increased 2 percent to 1.84
euros.  British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc  (BSY LN): Rupert
Murdoch-led News Corp. and the U.K.’s largest pay-television
operator need to respond to U.K. regulator Ofcom’s request for
information on their proposed merger by Nov. 19, Ofcom said in a
statement. The stock advanced 0.8 percent to 711.5 pence.  Corio NV  (CORA NA): The largest Dutch property developer
said third-quarter net income rose 75 percent to 78.1 million
euros after the value of its shopping centers increased. Corio
increased 0.4 percent to 51.93 euros.  Criteria Caixacorp SA  (CRI SM): The investment holding
company for La Caixa is scheduled to release its third-quarter
earnings. The shares rose 0.2 percent to 4.05 euros.  EDP-Energias de Portugal SA  (EDP PL): The country’s biggest
power company said nine-month net income rose 3.5 percent to 774
million euros. The utility said it’s cutting its average annual
investment target for 2011 and 2012 to 2.1 billion euros from an
earlier forecast of 2.4 billion euros. The shares fell 0.5
percent to 2.66 euros.  Fiat SpA  (F IM): The carmaker said Standard & Poor’s
assigned a preliminary BB+ rating with a negative outlook to
Fiat Industrial, the unit that Chief Executive Sergio Marchionne
is spinning off. The shares increased 2.7 percent to 12.52
euros.  Grifols SA  (GRF SM): Europe’s largest maker of blood-plasma
products said Spain’s regulator approved its purchase of U.S.-
based Talecris Biotherapeutics Holding Corp. The shares dropped
2 percent to 10.64 euros.  Groupe Bruxelles Lambert SA  (GBLB BB): The Belgian
investment firm controlled by billionaires Albert Frere and Paul
Desmarais reports nine-month earnings after the close of
trading. GBL climbed 2.7 percent to 65.61 euros.  M6 Metropole Television SA  (MMT FP): The television company
said sales rose 7.3 percent to 317.7 million euros in the third
quarter. The shares gained 2.3 percent to 18.6 euros.  Smith & Nephew Plc  (SN/ LN): Europe’s largest maker of
shoulder and knee implants may report third-quarter net income
of $125.3 million, according to the average of six estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. The shares rose 1.1 percent to 558.5
pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
